Word 2000's native HTML support appears to not support the CSS syntax for applying styles to the children of an element specified by a particular class. For example, the issue word export has the following style class:

{code:html}
    .tableBorder td, .grid td
    {
        vertical-align: top;
        padding: 2px;
        border: 10pt solid #cccccc;
    }
{code}

This should render all {{<td>}} elements under a {{<table class="tableBorder">}} element with the specified style, but doesn't under MS-Word 2000. 

It appears to have been fixed in Word 2003.

{code:title=SetComponentAndVersion.java|borderStyle=solid}
public class SetComponentAndVersion implements FunctionProvider
{
    /**
     * Automatically assign subtasks the same component/version as parent task.
     */
    public void execute (Map transientVars, Map args, PropertySet ps)
        throws WorkflowException
    {
        MutableIssue task = (MutableIssue)transientVars.get("issue");
        
        if (task.isSubTask())
        {
            ComponentManager componentManager = ComponentManager.getInstance();
            IssueManager issueManager = componentManager.getIssueManager();
            MutableIssue parent = issueManager.getIssueObject(task.getParentId());
            
            task.setComponents(parent.getComponents());
            task.setFixVersions(parent.getFixVersions());
            task.store();
        }
    }
}
{code} 

Fairly simple and straight forward.  I have access to the components and versions from the parent task, but they are not set successfully on the child task.

